  "Initiated By" : "FINRA",
  "Allegations" : "WILLFULLY VIOLATED SECTION 10(B) OF THE SECURITIES EXCHANGE ACT OF 1934, RULE 10B-5 THEREUNDER, VIOLATED FINRA RULES 2010, 2020, 2150, 3240, 8210, NASD RULES 2110, 2120, 2330, 3040 - BRIAN BORAKOWSKI SOLICITED CUSTOMERS TO PURCHASE PROMISSORY NOTES IN A LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY AND FALSELY REPRESENTED TO CUSTOMERS THAT BY PURCHASING PROMISSORY NOTES IN THE COMPANY, THEIR INVESTMENT WOULD BE USED TO PURCHASE VEHICLES AT U.S. AUTO AUCTIONS AND TO EXPORT THE VEHICLES TO RUSSIA FOR RE-SALE. INSTEAD OF INVESTING THE FUNDS AS REPRESENTED, BORAKOWSKI USED THE FUNDS TO PAY FOR BUSINESS EXPENSES RELATED TO HIS BRANCH OFFICE BUSINESS AND TO PAY PERSONAL EXPENSES. TO FURTHER HIS PONZI SCHEME, BORAKOWSKI USED INVESTORS' FUNDS TO MAKE PAYMENTS TO EARLIER INVESTORS. THE CUSTOMERS DID NOT KNOW BORAKOWSKI USED FUNDS TO MAKE PAYMENTS TO EARLIER INVESTORS AND DID NOT AUTHORIZE HIM TO DO SO. ALL BUT ONE INVESTOR RECEIVED PROMISSORY NOTES THAT BORE DIFFERENT INTEREST RATES WITH DIFFERENT MATURITY DATES. INVESTORS' FUNDS WERE DEPOSITED INTO AN ACCOUNT FOR THE COMPANY THAT BORAKOWSKI CONTROLLED. BORAKOWSKI, WHILE ASSOCIATED WITH A MEMBER FIRM, SOLD PROMISSORY NOTES TOTALING $665,900 TO INVESTORS WHO WERE CUSTOMERS OF HIS MEMBER FIRM AND DID NOT PROVIDE THE FIRM WITH PRIOR WRITTEN NOTIFICATION DESCRIBING THE PROPOSED TRANSACTIONS AND HIS PROPOSED ROLE THEREIN. BORAKOWSKI DID NOT RECEIVE WRITTEN PERMISSION TO PARTICIPATE IN THE SALE OF THE PROMISSORY NOTES. BORAKOWSKI BORROWED $11,500 FROM A NON-FAMILY MEMBER AND CUSTOMER OF HIS FIRM BUT DID NOT RECEIVE APPROVAL FROM HIS FIRM. BORAKOWSKI SENT THE CUSTOMER A CHECK DRAWN ON THE COMPANY'S BANK ACCOUNT IN THE AMOUNT OF $500 BUT DID NOT REPAY THE OUTSTANDING $12,000 BALANCE OWED ON THE LOAN. BORAKOWSKI COMPLETED A BRANCH AUDIT QUESTIONNAIRE AND FALSELY ANSWERED THE QUESTION REGARDING BORROWING OR LOANING MONEY OR SECURITIES FROM OR TO ANY CUSTOMER, EXCLUDING IMMEDIATE FAMILY MEMBERS. BORAKOWSKI FAILED TO RESPOND TO FINRA REQUESTS FOR INFORMATION, PREVENTING THE FINRA STAFF FROM PURSUING CERTAIN MATERIAL AREAS OF ITS INVESTIGATION.",
