  "Regulator Statement" : "DEFAULT DECISION RENDERED AUGUST 8, 2013 WHEREIN BORAKOWSKI IS BARRED FROM ASSOCIATION WITH ANY FINRA MEMBER IN ANY CAPACITY FOR WILLFULLY MAKING MATERIAL MISSTATEMENTS AND OMITTING MATERIAL FACTS IN CONNECTION WITH THE PURCHASE OF A SECURITY, IN VIOLATION OF SECTION 10(B) OF THE EXCHANGE ACT, RULE 10B-5 THEREUNDER, NASD RULES 2120 AND 2110, AND FINRA RULES 2020 AND 2010; CONVERTING CUSTOMER FUNDS, IN VIOLATION OF NASD RULES 2330 AND 2110, AND FINRA RULES 2010 AND 2150; ENGAGING IN PRIVATE SECURITIES TRANSACTIONS WITHOUT INFORMING HIS FINRA MEMBER FIRMS, IN VIOLATION OF NASD RULES 3040 AND 2110, AND FINRA RULE 2010; AND FAILING TO RESPOND TO REQUESTS FOR INFORMATION, IN VIOLATION OF FINRA RULES 8210 AND 2010. THE BARS SHALL BECOME EFFECTIVE IMMEDIATELY IF THIS DECISION BECOMES FINRA'S FINAL DISCIPLINARY ACTION. FOR ENTERING INTO AN IMPERMISSIBLE BORROWING ARRANGEMENT WITH A CLIENT, IN VIOLATION OF FINRA RULES 3240 AND 2010, BORAKOWSKI IS SUSPENDED FOR ONE YEAR, BUT THE SUSPENSION WILL NOT BE IMPOSED IN LIGHT OF THE BARS IMPOSED FOR HIS OTHER MISCONDUCT. FOR PROVIDING FALSE INFORMATION TO HIS FIRM, BORAKOWSKI IS ALSO SUSPENDED FOR ONE YEAR, BUT THE SUSPENSION WILL NOT BE IMPOSED IN LIGHT OF THE BARS IMPOSED FOR HIS OTHER MISCONDUCT. DECISION BECAME FINAL SEPTEMBER 5, 2013."
